# Just and CMake shortcuts

Use these when suggesting shell commands so the user can run less typing and stay consistent with the project.

## Justfile shortcuts

| Instead of | Use | When suggesting |
|------------|-----|------------------|
| `just build` | `just build` or `just b` (if alias) | Build in debug |
| (none) | `just pre-push` | Before git push (format + lint + test + build) |
| (none) | `just tag-ok` | Tag current commit as last known-good build |
| (none) | `just pull-safe` | Pull with uncommitted changes (stash → pull → pop) |
| long path | `r` or `cd $(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)` | Commands that must run from repo root |
| `ninja -C build` | `just build` | Build |
| (none) | `build:ai-friendly` or `./scripts/build_ai_friendly.sh` | Quiet build + JSON result (for tools/AI) |
| (none) | `build:ai-friendly-json` or `./scripts/build_ai_friendly.sh --json-only` | Build, print only JSON to stdout |
| (none) | Presets `*-debug-ai` (e.g. `macos-arm64-debug-ai`) | Configure with BUILD_AI_FRIENDLY=ON (JSON compiler diagnostics) |
| `./proto/generate.sh` (C++ only) | Not needed for C++ | C++ proto is generated at build by CMake; run `./proto/generate.sh` for Python/Go/TS |
| `ctest --test-dir build --output-on-failure` | `just test` | Run C++ tests |
| `./scripts/run_linters.sh` | `just lint` | Lint |
| `./scripts/run_linters.sh` + shellcheck on scripts | `just lint-shell` | Lint shell scripts + ansible/run-dev-setup.sh |
| `find ... clang-format -i` | `just format` | Format C++ |
| `./scripts/build_universal.sh` | `just build-universal` | Universal binary |
| `./scripts/verify_toolchain.sh` | `just verify-toolchain` | Verify C++ toolchain |
| `./ansible/run-dev-setup.sh` | `just ansible-dev` | Ansible dev setup (SSL fix on macOS) |
| (syntax-check playbook only) | `just ansible-check` | Ansible playbook syntax-check |

**Repo root:** From a subdir, use **`r`** (if you have `alias r='cd $(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)'` in ~/.zshrc) or **`cd $(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)`** before running just/scripts.

## Cursor commands

| Need | Command (Cursor command palette) |
|------|-----------------------------------|
| Pull with WIP | `git:pull-safe` |
| Build debug | `build:debug` |
| Build quiet + JSON result | `build:ai-friendly` |
| Build, JSON only to stdout | `build:ai-friendly-json` |
| Test | `test:run` |
| Lint | `lint:run` |
| Exarp tools | `exarp:tool` / `exarp:list-tools` |

## Checklist when suggesting commands

- [ ] Build → suggest `just build` (or `build:debug` in Cursor). For tools/AI: `build:ai-friendly` or `build:ai-friendly-json`.
- [ ] Proto C++ → no manual step; CMake generates at build. Python/Go/TS: `./proto/generate.sh`.
- [ ] Test → suggest `just test` or `test:run`.
- [ ] Lint → suggest `just lint` or `lint:run`.
- [ ] Pre-push → suggest `just pre-push`.
- [ ] Tag last good build → suggest `just tag-ok`.
- [ ] Pull but have uncommitted changes → suggest `git:pull-safe` or `just pull-safe`.
- [ ] Must run from repo root → suggest `r` (interactive) or `cd $(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)` (scripts).
